  "prompt": "What are 13.1 and 26.2 stickers and what do they mean?",
  "response": "These stickers are commonly found on cars, water bottles, and other personal items, and they represent the distances of half marathon (13.1 miles) and full marathon (26.2 miles) races.\n\n- 13.1 sticker: Indicates the person has completed a half marathon\n- 26.2 sticker: Indicates the person has completed a full marathon\n\nThese stickers are popular among runners as a way to show pride in their athletic achievement, demonstrating that they have trained for and completed a long-distance running event. The numbers represent the exact race distances:\n- Half marathon = 13.1 miles\n- Full marathon = 26.2 miles\n\nThey are similar to other athletic achievement stickers that showcase personal accomplishments in running and endurance sports.",
